===Etymology===
From the {{der|en|de|Berlin}}. Which is of {{der|de|sla|-}} origin, possibly from the {{der|de|pox|-}} stem {{m|pox|berl-}} / {{m|pox|birl-||swamp}} + suffix {{m|pox|-in}}, from {{der|de|sla-pro|-}}, from {{der|de|ine-pro|*ber|t=marshy, swampy place}}. The place is first mentioned by this name in the late 12th century (as {{cog|gml|Berlyn}}).

